HEADWORD: Saltness
<hw>Salt"ness</hw> <pr>(s⟦add⟧lt"n⟦ecr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
quality or state of being salt, or impregnated with salt; salt taste;
<as>as, the <ex>saltness</ex> of sea water</as>. In the sense of having
salt content, <altname>saltiness</altname> is more commonly
used.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> saltiness.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

